---
preview: **How many times a day do you write this import statement?**
title: Never `import React from ‘react’` again, thanks to Webpack’s ProvidePlugin
tags: JS
author: rrLero
date: 18-03-09 21:46
---
```
    new webpack.ProvidePlugin({
      'React':     'react'
    })
```

When Webpack builds your JavaScript, it will load the ‘react’ module whenever the identifier ‘React’ is declared in your code.